channel.title: And again... this time its the compiler
channel.description: Ok, well AGAIN (lol) I have an issue. Im able to get onto my server now, and so can others. I want to start editing it though, but as you all know in order for the editing to take place you need to compile... Well, I compile and it says "You don't have JDK 5.0 or JDK 6.0, go to mod tahroks blah blah.." Well, the thing is I do have JDK 6.0.17 (just downloaded it), and I do have tahroks perfect compiler. what is the problem?

item.title: And again... this time its the compiler
item.dc:creator: @own-u own-u
item.description:
@own-u wrote:

[quote=“jj0001, post:4, topic:317801”][quote author=own-u link=topic=414312.msg3050147#msg3050147 date=1260040189]
Well, now it says

Note:stream.java uses or overrides a depricated API.
Note:Recompile with -Xlint:deprecation for details.
Press any key to continue…
[/quote]That’s not a compiler error that’s just notes, It compiled fine and works.[/quote]

Ah. Well thanks a lot man
